  "title": "The Sunken Vault — Offering Chamber",
  "description": "This side-vault was built to receive the offering goods of the honoured dead — clay urns of oil, bundles of dried herbs, small figures of hammered tin. The urns have all been knocked from their shelves and shattered; the herbs are black dust; the tin figures are scattered across the floor like dropped coins. A cold that has nothing to do with the season sits in the corners of this room and does not disperse. The darkness here feels watched.",
